      "content": "got it. so the \"baseline\" is basically the classic western business look. but since my blog is global, how should i frame it when someone's traditional attire—like a sari, a dashiki, or a kimono—comes up in a high-level business meeting? should i present those as part of the \"standard\" for professional sophistication, or should i categorize them as something else so they don't clash with the \"elite\" look you described?",
